ter\"><script async src=\"//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<!-- Ad 4 -->\r\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-9716398444039739\" data-ad-slot=\"4680411731\"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n   (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script></p>\r\n<p>Simply, We can use the <code>Request</code> object. Just call its <code>ip()</code> method.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below an example:</p>\r\n\r\n[php]\r\n public function index(Request $request) {\r\n   $ip_address = $request-&gt;ip(); // return client ip\r\n }\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\n<p class=\'shr\'>That\'s it!. Please share your thoughts or suggestions in the comments below.</p>','How to get client ip address in laravel ?','','inherit','closed','closed','','94-revision-v1','','','2019-09-10 07:36:29','2019-09-10 02:06:29','',94,'https://nexladder.com/blog/94-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(277,1,'2019-09-10 07:38:41','2019-09-10 02:08:41','<p>In this article, We\'ll see what is the difference between var and let in javascript ?</p>\n\n<p>Below an example will clarify the difference.</p>\n<p class=\"text-center\"><script async src=\"//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\n<!-- Ad 4 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-9716398444039739\" data-ad-slot=\"4680411731\"></ins>\n<script>\n   (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script></p>\n<p>The <code>var</code> statement declares a variable, optionally initializing it to a value.\nDemo: Statement - <code>Var</code></p>\n\n[php]\n    var x = 1;\n\n    if (x === 1) {\n      var x = 2;\n\n      console.log(x);\n      // expected output: 2\n    }\n\n    console.log(x);\n    // expected output: 2\n\n[/php]\n\n<p>The <code>let</code> statement declares a block scope local variable, optionally initializing it to a value.</p>\n\n<p>Demo: Statement - <code>Let</code></p>\n\n[php]\n let x = 1;\n\n if (x === 1) {\n   let x = 2;\n\n   console.log(x);\n   // expected output: 2\n  }\n\n   console.log(x);\n   // expected output: 1\n\n[/php]\n\n<p><code>let</code> allows you to declare variables that are limited in scope to the block, statement, or expression on which it is used. This is unlike the <code>var</code> keyword, which defines a variable globally, or locally to an entire function regardless of block scope.</p>\n\n<p>Variables declared by <code>let</code> have as their scope the block in which they are defined, as well as in any contained sub-blocks. In this way, <code>let</code> works very much like <code>var</code>. The main difference is that the scope of a <code>var</code> variable is the entire enclosing function</p>\n\n<p class=\'shr\'>That\'s it!. Please share your thoughts or suggestions in the comments below.</p>','difference between var and let in javascript ?','','inherit','closed','closed','','90-autosave-v1','','','2019-09-10 07:38:41','2019-09-10 02:08:41','',90,'https://nexladder.com/blog/90-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(278,1,'2019-09-10 07:38:42','2019-09-10 02:08:42','<p>In this article, We\'ll see how to replace a string in vue js?<p>\n<p>Below an example to replace a string from \"Morning\" to \"Evening\".</p>\n\n<p class=\"text-center\"><script async src=\"//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\n<!-- Ad 4 -->\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-9716398444039739\" data-ad-slot=\"4680411731\"></ins>\n<script>\n   (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script></p>\n\n<p>Every Vue application starts by creating a new Vue instance with the Vue function:</h2></p>\n[php]\n  var vm = new Vue ({ \n     // options\n  })\n[/php]\n\n<p><code>new Vue ({e1: \'#appContainer\'})</code> will instantiate a new Vue instance. It accepts an options object as a parameter. This object is central in Vue, and defines and controls data and behavior.It contains all the information needed to create Vue instances and components.</p>\n\n[php]\n    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n    &lt;html&gt;\n    &lt;head&gt;\n        &lt;title&gt;How to replace a string in Vue JS? - nexladder.com&lt;/title&gt;\n        &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/vue/dist/vue.js?v=1&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n    &lt;/head&gt;\n    &lt;body&gt;\n\n    &lt;div id=&quot;appContainer&quot;&gt;\n        &lt;div&gt;{{ message }}&lt;/div&gt;\n        &lt;button @click=&quot;replace()&quot;&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n\n    &lt;/body&gt;\n\n    &lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;\n        new Vue({\n          el: \'#appContainer\',\n          data: { \n              message:&quot;Good Morning!&quot;\n          },\n          methods:{\n                replace: function () {\n                    this.message = this.message.replace(&quot;Morning&quot;, &quot;Evening&quot;);    \n                }\n          }\n        });\n    &lt;/script&gt;\n    &lt;/html&gt;\n[/php]\n\n<p class=\'shr\'>That\'s it!. Please share your thoughts or suggestions in the comments below.</p>','How to replace a string in vue js ?','','inherit','closed','closed','','86-autosave-v1','','','2019-09-10 07:38:42','2019-09-10 02:08:42','',86,'https://nexladder.com/blog/86-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2019-09-10 07:38:55','2019-09-10 02:08:55','<p>In this article, We\'ll see how to replace a string in vue js?</p>\r\n<p>Below an example to replace a string from \"Morning\" to \"Evening\".</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-center\"><script async src=\"//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<!-- Ad 4 -->\r\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-9716398444039739\" data-ad-slot=\"4680411731\"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n   (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</s