r is $sum&quot;;  // Output Sum of digits 12345 is 15\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\n<p class=\'shr\'>That\'s it!. Please share your thoughts or suggestions in the comments below.</p>','Write a program to calculate the sum of digits in php','','inherit','closed','closed','','138-revision-v1','','','2019-09-12 20:35:36','2019-09-12 15:05:36','',138,'https://nexladder.com/blog/138-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(301,1,'2019-09-12 20:35:45','2019-09-12 15:05:45','<p>In this article, We\'ll write a program to check the number is palindrome or not.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>Palindrome</code> number is a number which remains same when its digits are reversed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, number 123321 is a palindrome number. after reversed we\'ll get the same number.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\"><script async src=\"//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js\"></script>\r\n<!-- Ad 4 -->\r\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-9716398444039739\" data-ad-slot=\"4680411731\"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n   (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[php]\r\n    $number   = 123321;\r\n    $sum      = 0;\r\n    $pass_num = $number;\r\n    while (floor($pass_num)) {  \r\n      $rem = $pass_num % 10;  \r\n      $sum = $sum * 10 + $rem;  \r\n      $pass_num = $pass_num/10;  \r\n    } \r\n    if ($number == $sum)\r\n    echo &quot;$number is a palindrome number&quot;;\r\n    else\r\n    echo &quot;$number is a not palindrome number&quot;;\r\n\r\n   // Output 123321 is a palindrome number\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\n<p class=\'shr\'>That\'s it!. Please share your thoughts or suggestions in the comments below.</p>','Write a program to check number is palindrome or not','','inherit','closed','closed','','136-revision-v1','','','2019-09-12 20:35:45','2019-09-12 15:05:45','',136,'https://nexladder.com/blog/136-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(302,1,'2019-09-12 20:35:55','2019-09-12 15:05:55','<p>